1\">[</bpt>Data Conversion<ept id=\"p1\">](#data_conversion)</ept> section provides information about converters.","pos":[6288,6374],"source":" The [Data Conversion](#data_conversion) section provides information about converters."},{"pos":[6381,6456],"content":"When the user clicks the <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>Add Product<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> button, the following form comes up:","source":"When the user clicks the *Add Product* button, the following form comes up:"},{"pos":[6463,6609],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">![</bpt>Add Product Listing page<ept id=\"p1\">]</ept><bpt id=\"p2\">(../../../../docs/framework/wpf/data/media/databinding-demo-addproductlisting.png \"</bpt>DataBinding_Demo_AddProductListing<ept id=\"p2\">\")</ept>","source":"![Add Product Listing page](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/data/media/databinding-demo-addproductlisting.png \"DataBinding_Demo_AddProductListing\")"},{"content":"The user can edit the fields in the form, preview the product listing using the short preview and the more detailed preview panes, and then click <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>submit<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> to add the new product listing.","pos":[6616,6802],"source":"The user can edit the fields in the form, preview the product listing using the short preview and the more detailed preview panes, and then click *submit* to add the new product listing."},{"content":"Any existing grouping, filtering and sorting functionalities will apply to the new entry.","pos":[6803,6892]},{"content":"In this particular case, the item entered in the above image will be displayed as the second item within the <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>Computer<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> category.","pos":[6893,7022],"source":" In this particular case, the item entered in the above image will be displayed as the second item within the *Computer* category."},{"content":"Not shown in this image is the validation logic provided in the <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>Start Date<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox&gt;</ph>.","pos":[7029,7145],"source":"Not shown in this image is the validation logic provided in the *Start Date* <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox>."},{"content":"If the user enters an invalid date (invalid formatting or a past date), the user will be notified with a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.ToolTip&gt;</ph> and a red exclamation point next to the <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox&gt;</ph>.","pos":[7146,7369],"source":" If the user enters an invalid date (invalid formatting or a past date), the user will be notified with a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ToolTip> and a red exclamation point next to the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox>."},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Data Validation<ept id=\"p1\">](#data_validation)</ept> section discusses how to create validation logic.","pos":[7370,7459],"source":" The [Data Validation](#data_validation) section discusses how to create validation logic."},{"pos":[7466,7736],"content":"Before going into the different features of data binding outlined above, we will first discuss in the next section the fundamental concepts that are critical to understanding <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_winclient](../../../../includes/tla2sharptla-winclient-md.md)]</ph> data binding.","source":"Before going into the different features of data binding outlined above, we will first discuss in the next section the fundamental concepts that are critical to understanding [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_winclient](../../../../includes/tla2sharptla-winclient-md.md)] data binding."},{"pos":[7745,7772],"content":"Basic Data Binding Concepts","linkify":"Basic Data Binding Concepts","nodes":[{"content":"Basic Data Binding Concepts","pos":[0,27]}]},{"content":"Regardless of what element you are binding and the nature of your data source, each binding always follows the model illustrated by the following figure:","pos":[7779,7932]},{"pos":[7939,8059],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">![</bpt>Basic data binding diagram<ept id=\"p1\">]</ept><bpt id=\"p2\">(../../../../docs/framework/wpf/data/media/databindingmostbasic.png \"</bpt>DataBindingMostBasic<ept id=\"p2\">\")</ept>","source":"![Basic data binding diagram](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/data/media/databindingmostbasic.png \"DataBindingMostBasic\")"},{"content":"As illustrated by the above figure, data binding is essentially the bridge between your binding target and your binding source.","pos":[8066,8193]},{"content":"The figure demonstrates the following fundamental <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_winclient](../../../../includes/tla2sharptla-winclient-md.md)]</ph> data binding concepts:","pos":[8194,8348],"source":" The figure demonstrates the following fundamental [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_winclient](../../../../includes/tla2sharptla-winclient-md.md)] data binding concepts:"},{"content":"Typically, each binding has these four components: a binding target object, a target property, a binding source, and a path to the value in the binding source to use.","pos":[8358,8524]},{"content":"For example, if you want to bind the content of a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox&gt;</ph> to the <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>Name<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> property of an <bpt id=\"p2\">*</bpt>Employee<ept id=\"p2\">*</ept> object, your target object is the <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox&gt;</ph>, the target property is the <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox.Text%2A&gt;</ph> property, the value to use is <bpt id=\"p3\">*</bpt>Name<ept id=\"p3\">*</ept>, and the source object is the <bpt id=\"p4\">*</bpt>Employee<ept id=\"p4\">*</ept> object.","pos":[8525,8887],"source":" For example, if you want to bind the content of a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox> to the *Name* property of an *Employee* object, your target object is the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox>, the target property is the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox.Text%2A> property, the value to use is *Name*, and the source object is the *Employee* object."},{"content":"The target property must be a dependency property.","pos":[8897,8947]},{"content":"Most <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.UIElement&gt;</ph> properties are dependency properties and most dependency properties, except read-only ones, support data binding by default.","pos":[8948,9109],"source":" Most <xref:System.Windows.UIElement> properties are dependency properties and most dependency properties, except read-only ones, support data binding by default."},{"content":"(Only <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.DependencyObject&gt;</ph> types can define dependency properties and all <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.UIElement&gt;</ph>s derive from <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.DependencyObject&gt;</ph>.)","pos":[9110,9287],"source":" (Only <xref:System.Windows.DependencyObject> types can define dependency properties and all <xref:System.Windows.UIElement>s derive from <xref:System.Windows.DependencyObject>.)"},{"content":"Although not specified in the figure, it should be noted that the binding source object is not restricted to being a custom <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_clr](../../../../includes/tla2sharptla-clr-md.md)]</ph> object.","pos":[9297,9498],"source":"Although not specified in the figure, it should be noted that the binding source object is not restricted to being a custom [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_clr](../../../../includes/tla2sharptla-clr-md.md)] object."},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_winclient](../../../../includes/tla2sharptla-winclient-md.md)]</ph> data binding supports data in the form of <ph id=\"ph2\">[!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_clr](../../../../includes/tla2sharptla-clr-md.md)]</ph> objects and <ph id=\"ph3\">[!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xml](../../../../includes/tla2sharptla-xml-md.md)]</ph>.","pos":[9499,9775],"source":"[!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_winclient](../../../../includes/tla2sharptla-winclient-md.md)] data binding supports data in the form of [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_clr](../../../../includes/tla2sharptla-clr-md.md)] objects and [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xml](../../../../includes/tla2sharptla-xml-md.md)]."},{"content":"To provide some examples, your binding source may be a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.UIElement&gt;</ph>, any list object, a <ph id=\"ph2\">[!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_clr](../../../../includes/tla2sharptla-clr-md.md)]</ph> object that is associated with <ph id=\"ph3\">[!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_adonet](../../../../includes/tlasharptla-adonet-md.md)]</ph> data or Web Services, or an XmlNode that contains your <ph id=\"ph4\">[!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xml](../../../../includes/tla2sharptla-xml-md.md)]</ph> data.","pos":[9776,10188],"source":" To provide some examples, your binding source may be a <xref:System.Windows.UIElement>, any list object, a [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_clr](../../../../includes/tla2sharptla-clr-md.md)] object that is associated with [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_adonet](../../../../includes/tlasharptla-adonet-md.md)] data or Web Services, or an XmlNode that contains your [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xml](../../../../includes/tla2sharptla-xml-md.md)] data."},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Binding Sources Overview<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/data/binding-sources-overview.md)</ept>.","pos":[10189,10307],"source":" For more information, see [Binding Sources Overview](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/data/binding-sources-overview.md)."},{"content":"As you read through other <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_sdk](../../../../includes/tlasharptla-sdk-md.md)]</ph> topics, it is important to remember that when you are establishing a binding, you are binding a binding target <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>to<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> a binding source.","pos":[10314,10541],"source":"As you read through other [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_sdk](../../../../includes/tlasharptla-sdk-md.md)] topics, it is important to remember that when you are establishing a binding, you are binding a binding target *to* a binding source."},{"content":"For example, if you are displaying some underlying <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xml](../../../../includes/tla2sharptla-xml-md.md)]</ph> data in a <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.ListBox&gt;</ph> using data binding, you are binding your <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.ListBox&gt;</ph> to the <ph id=\"ph4\">[!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xml](../../../../includes/tla2sharptla-xml-md.md)]</ph> data.","pos":[10542,10874],"source":" For example, if you are displaying some underlying [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xml](../../../../includes/tla2sharptla-xml-md.md)] data in a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ListBox> using data binding, you are binding your <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ListBox> to the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xml](../../../../includes/tla2sharptla-xml-md.md)] data."},{"content":"To establish a binding, you use the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Data.Binding&gt;</ph> object.","pos":[10881,10959],"source":"To establish a binding, you use the <xref:System.Windows.Data.Binding> object."},{"content":"The rest of this topic discusses many of the concepts associated with and some of the properties and usage of the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Data.Binding&gt;</ph> object.","pos":[10960,11116],"source":" The rest of this topic discusses many of the concepts associated with and some of the properties and usage of the <xref:System.Windows.Data.Binding> object."},{"pos":[11167,11193],"content":"Direction of the Data Flow","linkify":"Direction of the Data Flow","nodes":[{"content":"Direction of the Data Flow","pos":[0,26]}]},{"content":"As mentioned previously and as indicated by the arrow in the figure above, the data flow of a binding can go from the binding target to the binding source (for example, the source value changes when a user edits the value of a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox&gt;</ph>) and/or from the binding source to the binding target (for example, your <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox&gt;<